==English==
===Preposition===
{{wikipedia}}
'''modulo'''
#{{mathematics}} [[equivalence]] with respect to a [[specified]] [[modulus]]
#:21 modulo 9 is 3 - because there is remainder of 3 left when 21 is divided by 9
#('''computing slang''') "adjusted for" or "except for"
#:The "tail recursion modulo cons" technique allows functions that would be tail recursive but for a cons call to be transformed into a tail recursive form.

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|modulo operation}}
'''modulo'''
#{{computing}} the [[operation]] or [[function]] that returns the [[remainder]] of one [[number]] divided by another

